canonical_structure.name: UBX-NAV-TIMETRUSTED
canonical_structure.description: External trusted time information. This message contains information about external trusted time received via assistance data (UBX-MGA-INI-TIME_UTC or UBX-MGA-INI-TIME_GNSS).

fields.name: refSys
fields.description: Reference time system (all the GNSS system supported by UBX-MGA-INI-TIME_GNSS except Glonass). 0: None, 1: GPS Time, 2: Galileo System Time (GST), 3: Beidou System Time (BDT), 15: NavIC System Time

bits.name: trustedTime
bits.description: 1 = Valid initial and propagated trusted time

bits.name: deltaTimeValid
bits.description: 1 = Valid delta time (deltas and deltaMs) between current estimated time and the propagated trusted time

fields.name: iTOW
fields.description: GPS time of week of the navigation epoch.

fields.name: propWno
fields.description: Week number propagating the initial trusted time

fields.name: propTow
fields.description: Time of week propagating the initial trusted time

fields.name: deltas
fields.description: Integer seconds of delta time (current estimated time minus propagated trusted time)

fields.name: deltaMs
fields.description: Integer milliseconds of delta time (current estimated time minus propagated trusted time)

adjudication.reasoning: The provided extraction is complete and consistent with standard UBX protocol structures for the NAV class. The offsets align with the data types (e.g., U4/I4 at 4-byte boundaries, U2 at 2-byte boundaries) and the total payload length of 40 bytes is correctly accounted for. The bitfield definitions and reference systems are clearly defined and typical for u-blox HPG (High Precision GNSS) documentation.
